So.. Im moving blogs, Ill still use this one for more personal stuff but since my widgets on the mac connect directly to Blogger, which also connects to my google account and picasa.. the daily stuff, knowledge gathered and insights will go to the leftamessage blog.

If you have gmail and want to follow, please do =)&nbsp;

Ive had this friend through a blog journal who ive been following for a couple years... she was moving to new zealand when i first found her blog so i followed it cos it was interesting. She was around my age when she passed away this week, she moved to new zealand, started her own Mac business, filmed a documentary about her ordeal moving, getting married, and discovering she had cancer... leukemia.
 
 its weird because as there are many people we all interact with online sometimes casually sometimes more, even people on here ..you get a glimpse of their personality sometimes and more.. Melanie wrote at lengths about her leukemia and about her move and about all the things she was looking forward and it feels odd that her life has extinguished. It makes me mad that something like cancer can strike someone who was healthy, happy and living well. I know its not a &quot;typical&quot; death as in a friend you actually knew in real life but its still feels uncomfortable and sad, because for a brief moment you read the thoughts and feelings of someone as if they were a close friend...
 
 &quot;There are no certainties, only opportunities.
 We are here to help each other get through this thing, whatever it is.&quot;
 -Melanie aka &quot;Luminel&quot;
